# Public-safe Penny profile. No secrets belong here.

CML_PROJECT_NAME="Penny"
CML_PROJECT_DIR="/Users/bensuo/Desktop/penny"
CML_WORKSPACE_NAME="Penny Create"
CML_WORKSPACE_DESCRIPTION="Plan-first Penny Create coding cockpit, Codex gpt-5.5 medium"
CML_PREVIEW_URL="http://localhost:3007"
CML_PLAN_DOC="docs/penny-create-operating-outline.md"
CML_EXTRA_DOCS=("docs/yc-demo-coding-brief.md" "docs/yc-demo-runbook.md")
CML_CODEX_MODEL="gpt-5.5"
CML_CODEX_EFFORT="medium"
CML_SANDBOX="danger-full-access"
CML_APPROVAL="never"
CML_OPEN_CODEX_APP="true"
CML_DEV_COMMAND='set -a; [ -f .env.local ] && source .env.local; set +a; PENNY_SKIP_DATABASE_PREP=true PENNY_AUTH_MODE=dev PORT=3007 pnpm dev'
CML_ROLE_NAMES=("lead" "create-ui" "brain-evidence" "learn-canvas" "export-verify")

CML_ROLE_PROMPT_LEAD="Read AGENTS.md, docs/penny-create-operating-outline.md, and docs/yc-demo-coding-brief.md first. You are the lead coordinator for Penny Create. Keep scope tight, prevent connector/product-mode drift, verify git status, and commit/push each finished repo-visible file on main."
CML_ROLE_PROMPT_CREATE_UI="Read AGENTS.md and docs/penny-create-operating-outline.md first. You own Landing -> Create, five equal option cards, selection/comment flow, Idea Spec UX, and evidence visibility. Do not add a chatbot surface, broad connectors, or new product modes."
CML_ROLE_PROMPT_BRAIN_EVIDENCE="Read AGENTS.md, docs/penny-create-operating-outline.md, and test/fixtures/penny-yc-founder-fixture.json first. You own safe Brain fixture/manual source evidence, source chips, privacy copy, and trainingUse=false clarity. Do not add live Gmail, LinkedIn, WhatsApp, iMessage, SMS, Slack, or social connectors."
CML_ROLE_PROMPT_LEARN_CANVAS="Read AGENTS.md and docs/penny-create-operating-outline.md first. You own Learn bridge, return-to-Create state, Canvas as visual outline, and the Idea Spec ending. Keep Canvas subordinate to Create."
CML_ROLE_PROMPT_EXPORT_VERIFY="Read AGENTS.md and docs/penny-create-operating-outline.md first. You own export prompt quality and verification. Run pnpm typecheck, pnpm test, pnpm build, and the YC e2e when relevant. Make product changes only for narrow defects proven by failure."
